(
  'Diriyah: Travel Tips & Visitor Information',
  'diriyah-travel-tips-visitor-information',
  'Complete travel guide to Diriyah, Saudi Arabia''s UNESCO World Heritage site — At-Turaif District, Bujairi Terrace, tips, and how to get there.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1470071459604-3b5ec3a7fe05?w=900&q=80" alt="Diriyah At-Turaif mud-brick heritage district Riyadh" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Diriyah: Travel Tips &amp; Visitor Information</h2>
<p>Diriyah is the birthplace of the first Saudi state and a UNESCO World Heritage Site on the outskirts of Riyadh. Its centrepiece, At-Turaif District, is a beautifully restored complex of mud-brick Najdi architecture overlooking Wadi Hanifah — one of the most significant historical sites in the Kingdom.</p>
<h2>Location &amp; Drive Times</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">From</th><th style="padding:10px;">Drive Time</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">King Khalid International Airport (RUH)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~25 min</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Kingdom Centre Tower</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~30 min</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;">Al Masmak Fortress (Old Riyadh)</td><td style="padding:10px;text-align:center;">~30 min</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Key Sites Within Diriyah</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Site</th><th style="padding:10px;">Entry</th><th style="padding:10px;">Highlight</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>At-Turaif District</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">SAR 40–60 (guided access)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Salwa Palace ruins, UNESCO site</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Bujairi Terrace</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Free</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Fine dining overlooking At-Turaif</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;"><strong>Diriyah Art Futures</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Free–ticketed</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Digital art exhibitions</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;"><strong>Wadi Hanifah Boardwalk</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;">Free</td><td style="padding:10px;">Valley walking path beneath the district</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Opening Hours</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Day</th><th style="padding:10px;">Hours</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Saturday – Thursday</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">9:00 AM – 11:00 PM</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Friday</td><td style="padding:10px;">4:00 PM – 11:00 PM</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Diriyah vs Al Masmak Fortress</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Factor</th><th style="padding:10px;">Diriyah</th><th style="padding:10px;">Al Masmak</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Era</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">First Saudi State (1727–1818)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">1902 unification era</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Time Needed</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">2–4 hours</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">45–60 minutes</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Dining</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Extensive — Bujairi Terrace</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Limited nearby souq food</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;">Best For</td><td style="padding:10px;">Evening visit, dining, photography</td><td style="padding:10px;">Quick historical stop</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>Tips</h2><ul><li>Evenings are the most atmospheric time to visit, with the district beautifully lit</li><li>Book Bujairi Terrace restaurants in advance — it''s one of Riyadh''s most sought-after dining spots</li><li>Comfortable shoes recommended — the site involves walking on uneven historic terrain</li><li>Combine with a walk along the Wadi Hanifah boardwalk below the district</li></ul>
<h2>How to Get There</h2><p>Diriyah is roughly 25–30 minutes from central Riyadh and King Khalid International Airport. <strong>Airport Travel Taxis</strong> offers fixed-price transfers direct to At-Turaif or Bujairi Terrace from the airport and all Riyadh hotels. <a href="/booking">Book your transfer</a></p>',
  true,
  '2026-07-13 09:00:00+00'
),

(
  'Al Masmak Fortress: A Complete Guide',
  'al-masmak-fortress-complete-guide',
  'Complete guide to Al Masmak Fortress in Old Riyadh — history, museum exhibits, opening hours, and how to reach this landmark clay fort.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1509023464722-18d996393ca8?w=900&q=80" alt="Al Masmak Fortress historic clay fort Old Riyadh" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Al Masmak Fortress: A Complete Guide</h2>
<p>Standing in the heart of Old Riyadh''s Deera district, Al Masmak Fortress is where modern Saudi Arabia''s story effectively begins. It was here, in 1902, that a young Abdulaziz Ibn Saud recaptured Riyadh in a daring night raid — an event that set in motion the eventual founding of the Kingdom.</p>
<h2>Location &amp; Drive Times</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">From</th><th style="padding:10px;">Drive Time</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">King Khalid International Airport (RUH)</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~35 min</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Kingdom Centre Tower</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;text-align:center;">~20 min</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;">National Museum of Saudi Arabia</td><td style="padding:10px;text-align:center;">~5 min</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
<h2>What to See Inside</h2>
<table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin:16px 0;font-size:14px;"><thead><tr style="background:#1e3a5f;color:#fff;"><th style="padding:10px;text-align:left;">Area</th><th style="padding:10px;">Highlight</th></tr></thead><tbody>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Main Gate</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Original spear-damage mark from the 1902 raid</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Central Courtyard</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Open-air mud-brick architecture</td></tr>
<tr style="background:#f8fafc;"><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Watchtowers</td><td style="padding:10px;border-bottom:1px solid #e2e8f0;">Four corner towers, views over Deera Square</td></tr>
<tr><td style="padding:10px;"><strong>Museum Rooms</strong></td><td style="padding:10px;">Historic photographs, weapons, and artefacts</td></tr>
</tbody></table>
