</tbody></table>
<h2>Recommended Old Riyadh Itinerary</h2>
<div style="background:#f0f9ff;border:1px solid #bae6fd;border-radius:12px;padding:16px;margin:16px 0;"><p style="font-weight:600;margin-bottom:8px;">Half-Day Heritage Walk</p><ul style="margin:0;padding-left:20px;font-size:14px;"><li><strong>9:00 AM</strong> — Al Masmak Fortress</li><li><strong>10:00 AM</strong> — Deera Square &amp; Souq Al Zal</li><li><strong>11:00 AM</strong> — National Museum of Saudi Arabia</li><li><strong>1:00 PM</strong> — Lunch in Old Riyadh</li></ul></div>
<h2>Tips</h2><ul><li>Free entry makes this an easy add-on to any Old Riyadh itinerary</li><li>Souq Al Zal, a traditional market, sits right next to the fortress — worth a browse</li><li>Modest dress is appropriate throughout the historic district</li><li>Early morning visits avoid both the heat and the crowds</li></ul>
<h2>How to Get There</h2><p>Al Masmak Fortress sits in Deera Square in the historic heart of Riyadh. <strong>Airport Travel Taxis</strong> offers fixed-price transfers from King Khalid International Airport and all Riyadh hotels. <a href="/booking">Book your transfer</a></p>',
