(
  'Edge of the World Riyadh: Everything You Need to Know',
  'edge-of-the-world-riyadh-everything-you-need-to-know',
  'Everything you need to know about the Edge of the World near Riyadh — the dramatic Jebel Fihrayn cliffs, hiking tips, and transport options.',
  '<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1500534623283-312aade485b7?w=900&q=80" alt="Edge of the World Jebel Fihrayn cliffs near Riyadh" style="width:100%;border-radius:16px;margin-bottom:24px;max-height:400px;object-fit:cover;"/>
<h2>Edge of the World Riyadh: Everything You Need to Know</h2>
<p>Roughly 90 minutes northwest of Riyadh, the Edge of the World (Jebel Fihrayn) is one of Saudi Arabia''s most dramatic natural landmarks — a jagged escarpment where the Tuwaiq Mountains drop away suddenly, leaving sweeping cliff-top views across the desert that seem to stretch to the horizon.</p>
<h2>Location &amp; Drive Times</h2>
